    <text id="B0370T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Nelson states that he will call on Jackson in a few days so that Jackson may
                    review his accounts as related to a dispute between Nelson and a Harner
                Green.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> Tho. P. Jackson</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-12-23"><abbr expan="December">Dec</abbr> 23rd 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Jennings Gap</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have <abbr expan="received">recd.</abbr> yours of the 21st by <orig
                        reg="Harner">Harman</orig>
                    <unclear>Green</unclear> (<abbr expan="colored">C</abbr>), &amp; reply by
                    note this morning as it is absolutely impossible for me to call in <hi
                        rend="underline">person</hi> just now. I will however say that I have
                        <unclear>offsets</unclear> against the <abbr expan="amount">amt.</abbr> he
                    claims, I will call ro see you in a few days &amp; let you examine my <abbr
                        expan="accounts">acts</abbr>.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours obediently</salute>
                    <signed>Robt. R. Nelson</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
